<h2>All the Users in Message App:</h2>
<br />
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Email</th>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Screen name</th>
    <th></th>
    <th></th>
    <th></th>
  </tr>

<% @users.each do |user| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= user.email %></td>
    <td><%= user.name %></td>
    <td><%= user.screen_name %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Show', user, :class => 'btn btn-small btn-success' %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_user_path(user), :class => 'btn btn-small btn-inverse' %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', user, :class => 'btn btn-small btn-danger', method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' } %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
</table>

<br />

<%= link_to 'New User', new_user_path, :class => 'btn btn-large btn-success' %>
<div><br /></div>
<p>To make things simple and focused on the goal of user messaging, there is no authentication here, so we're going to pretend a bit. By switching between user Show actions, we can pretend we're logged into a user's home page, and then create, read, and destroy messages.</p>